Eggdrop Features
================

IRC bot capabilities:

  - IRCv3 capability negotiation: account-notify, account-tag,
    away-notify, cap-notify, chghost, echo-message, extended-join,
    invite-notify, message-tags, monitor, SASL, server-time, setname,
    userhost-in-names, WHOX, +typing
  - IRCX/Ophion protocol: CREATE, PROP, ACCESS, +q channel owner
  - TLS 1.2/1.3 for server and botnet connections (bundled opssl)
  - SASL authentication: PLAIN, EXTERNAL, SCRAM-SHA-256/512,
    ECDSA-NIST256P, ECDH-X25519
  - IPv6 support
  - Twitch IRC support
  - Botnet: link bots to share user/ban/exempt/invite/ignore lists
  - Channel management: bans, exempts, invites, flood protection
  - DCC chat and file transfer
  - User database with per-channel access flags and passwords

Scripting:

  - Python API: 239 commands, 100% parity with Tcl
  - Tcl API: full bind system, timer callbacks, Tcl procs
  - Decorator-based Python binds via scripts/eggtools.py
  - Tcl is optional — Python can be the sole scripting engine
  - 21 built-in modules (irc, server, channels, dns, blowfish, ...)

Configuration:

  - TOML format: clean key=value syntax, no Tcl knowledge needed
  - Interactive setup wizard: eggdrop --setup
  - Per-channel settings via [[chanset]] blocks
  - Auto-create userfile on first run with TOML configs
  - Legacy .conf files still supported

Platform support:

  - Five native I/O backends: io_uring (Linux), epoll (Linux),
    kqueue (macOS/BSD), IOCP (Windows), select (fallback)
  - Runs on Linux, macOS, FreeBSD, OpenBSD, NetBSD, Windows
    (MinGW, MSVC), and Cygwin

Storage:

  - Pluggable backend: LMDB (crash-safe, default) or flat-file
  - LMDB auto-recovers userfile after crash
  - Per-user/host/account/ignore sub-databases for direct lookups

Security:

  - CSPRNG: getrandom(2) / arc4random_buf for all random values
  - PBKDF2-SHA256 password hashing
  - Complete string safety: zero raw strcpy/sprintf/strcat/atoi/
    gets/strtok/strncpy/strncat/system/unbounded-sscanf remaining
  - Build hardening: stack protector, FORTIFY_SOURCE, full RELRO

Performance:

  - O(1) hash tables for channel members, bans, bind dispatch
  - Slab allocator for hot-path allocations
  - CIDR trie for O(k) ban matching
  - LTO for cross-file inlining and dead-code elimination
  - Atomic traffic counters

Testing:

  - 7 test executables covering core subsystems
  - All tests pass under ASAN + UBSAN sanitiser builds
  - Zero compiler warnings on GCC 15


